To enhance the ability of graduate students in the College of Forestry to efficiently read and analyze scientific papers, the College of Forestry Graduate Student Association successfully hosted a “Special Lecture on Scientific Paper Writing and Submission” in Room 116 of the Forestry Science Building on December 11.  Nearly 100 graduate students from various disciplines within the School of Forestry attended the lecture. The presenter, Wang Chengyuan, a Class of 2024 student in the Forestry Management program, drew on his experience publishing nearly 20 SCI papers (including 8 top-tier papers and 1 highly cited paper). Using a “practical experience + systematic methodology” approach, he provided the attendees with comprehensive, hands-on guidance throughout the entire process, helping them overcome the academic challenges of “difficulty in writing and high rejection rates during submission.”

Thank for Zhilin Fang and Chen Wang invitation!!!
